(firstQuint)Compare Effect of Surgical Antiseptic Preparations on Incise Drape Adhesion to Skin.

 Adhesive incise drapes are often used to provide a physical sterile barrier between the surrounding skin and the open wound at the beginning of a surgery.

 This study sought to determine the effect of presurgical skin antiseptic preparation on the adhesion of various incise drapes to the skin.

